            . I am a <rs id="t18230514-101-viclabel529" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230514-101-victim907 t18230514-101-viclabel529"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18230514-101-crimeloc530">Upper East Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230514-101-crimeloc530" type="placeName" value="Upper East Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230514-101-crimeloc530" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230514-101-off527 t18230514-101-crimeloc530"></join>. On the 20th of April, at nine o'clock at night, I missed this bacon from the window, went out toward Butler's buildings, and in Brown Bear-alley, I saw Cole with it; another man was with him. I called Stop thief! he threw it down, and ran into the officer's hands - the salt and meal off the bacon was on his jacket. I knew him before, and am certain of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230514-101-person909">
                  MARY 
                  WATKINSON
               <interp inst="t18230514-101-person909" type="surname" value="WATKINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230514-101-person909" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230514-101-person909" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Brown Bear-alley. I<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182305140036"></xptr>saw the prisoners pass with the bacon. Cohen helped it on Cole's back. I am certain of them both - there was a third man with them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230514-101-person910">
                  ELIZA 
                  PARKER
               <interp inst="t18230514-101-person910" type="surname" value="PARKER"></interp>
